DNSRecon ia very useful tool
 the DNS converts the domain name into an IP address and forwards the request for further processing

This conversion of a domain name into an IP address is performed using a record. 
Attackers perform a reverse DNS lookup on the IP range to locate a DNS PTR record for such IP addresses
Attackers use various tools such as DNSRecon, Reverse Lookup, puredns, Reverse IP Domain Check, and Reverse IP Lookup to perform reverse DNS lookup on the target host

DNSRecon is an inbuilt tool in the Kali Linux
User have to just write DNSRecon and the terminal open for it 
Command:- dnsrecon -r 162.241.216.0-162.241.216.255

-r option specifies the range of IP addresses (first to last) for a reverse lookup by brute force.
